<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"The degree of a graph vertex v of =
a graph G, also called the vertex degree or local degree, is the number of =
graph edges which touch v. The vertex degrees are illustrated above for a r=
andom graph. The vertex degree is also called the local degree or valency. =
The ordered list of vertex degrees in a given graph is called its degree se=
quence. A list of vertex degrees of a graph can be computed in the Wolfram =
Language using VertexDegree[g], and precomputed vertex degrees are availabl=
e for...">
